kind: llman.sdd.spec
name: "layer-architecture"
purpose: "TBD - created by archiving change c225-refactor-domain-layering. Update purpose after archive."
valid_scope[2]: src/,tests/
requirements[13]{req_id,title,statement}:
  la1,"core-layer","System MUST provide a base core/ layer hosting domain-core vocabulary types including AgentMessage and XyModel and XyTool and ModelKind and XyChunk and ALL pure data types consumed by two or more layers (such as SessionEntry variants, SourceInfo, SkillInfo, PromptTemplate, CompactionSettings, AgentLifecycleEvent) so that no layer must import crate::infra merely to reference a shared data type."
  la2,"downward-dependency","infra/ modules MUST NOT import any crate::agent symbol; agent/ modules MUST NOT import any concrete infra/ type (only via core ports); interactive/ modules MUST NOT import crate::agent or crate::infra except in the in-process composition root. core/ MUST have zero crate:: internal dependencies."
  la3,"arch-guard","System MUST enforce via a guard test that no file under src/infra imports crate::agent."
  la4,"interactive-rename",The interactive surface directory MUST be named interactive/ (not interface/); interface is reserved for the Rust trait concept.
  la5,"protocol-module","System MUST provide a protocol/ module as the single source of truth for client-core interaction: command enum (client to core), event enum (core to client), response envelope, and error codes."
  la6,"server-module","System MUST provide a server/ module that hosts agent + infra runtimes and exposes protocol/ over REST (/api/v1) and WebSocket; the server MUST enforce a single-instance lock."
  la7,"runtime-residence","All runtimes (provider, tool, session storage, exec-env, bash executor, secret resolution, resource loader) MUST live under infra/; agent/ MUST hold them only as Arc<dyn Port> injected at the composition root; agent/ MUST NOT call any infra constructor or borrow infra exec primitives directly."
  la8,"agent-independence","The Agent facade constructor MUST NOT require a Session, MUST NOT hold a session_id, and MUST NOT depend on Session persistence lifecycle; session_id is a SessionStore query key bound in the interactive layer."
  la9,"arch-guard-expanded","The architecture guard MUST enforce via a guard test (src/tests.rs::arch_guard) all of: no infra file imports crate::agent, no agent file imports ANY concrete crate::infra type via a full scan of crate::infra:: in production code (not limited to infra::provider::{openai,anthropic,fake,mock}), and no interactive file imports crate::agent or crate::infra except the in-process driver composition root; the scan scope MUST reconcile with la2 (agent imports no concrete infra type)."
  la10,"note-convention","Deliberate simplifications MUST be marked with a tool-agnostic comment of the form '// NOTE: <what>. ceiling: <when it breaks>. upgrade: <trigger>.' so they can be grepped and reaped."
  la11,"arch-guard-interactive","The architecture guard MUST verify that interactive/ (excluding the driver composition root and rpc.rs) does not import crate::agent or crate::infra types; once rpc.rs no longer needs AgentSession, remove it from exempt_files."
  la12,"arch-guard-allowlist","System MUST maintain a documented allowlist of pre-existing agent to infra import violations inside arch_guard; each allowlist entry MUST cite a follow-up change id that will remove it, and any NEW agent to infra production import not present in the allowlist MUST fail the guard."
  la13,"agent-thin-no-presentation","agent/ MUST NOT host pure presentation or user-guidance logic such as static help text or message formatting; such logic MUST live under interactive/ (the client surface), and agent/ MUST contain only the orchestration loop, hook points, and orchestration state."
scenarios[15]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  la1,"shared-types-in-core",a pure data type (e.g. SessionEntry or SourceInfo) is needed by both agent/ and infra/,the type is declared and imported,"both layers import it from crate::core and neither depends on crate::infra for the type"
  la2,"agent-no-infra-concrete",an agent/ source file is compiled,"it references crate::infra::provider::OpenAIProvider or crate::infra::tools::BashTool",the build or guard rejects it
  la2,"interactive-isolation",an interactive/ source file is compiled,"it references crate::agent:: or crate::infra::","the build or guard rejects it unless it is the in-process driver root"
  la3,"guard-catches-violation","a new src/infra file adds use crate::agent::session",the architecture guard runs,the guard fails and reports the offending file path
  la4,"dir-named-interactive",the source tree is inspected,src/interface no longer exists and src/interactive exists,the rename is complete
  la5,"protocol-commands",a client sends a command to the core,the command is serialized,"it deserializes into the protocol::Command enum defined in protocol/"
  la6,"single-instance",a second server process starts against the same lock path,it calls acquire_lock,it receives ServerLockedError
  la7,"executor-not-in-agent",the bash executor (process spawn + output streaming) is located,its source file is inspected,it lives under infra/ and agent/ reaches it only via an injected port or the composition root
  la8,"facade-no-session",the Agent facade is constructed,only port trait objects are passed,construction succeeds without a Session instance or session_id
  la9,"guard-catches-tools-leak","a new agent/ file adds use crate::infra::tools::BashTool or crate::infra::tools::accumulator in production code",the architecture guard runs,the guard fails and reports the offending file path even though it is not one of openai/anthropic/fake/mock
  la9,"guard-catches-provider-factory","a new agent/ file calls crate::infra::provider::factory::build_provider in production code",the architecture guard runs,the guard fails because the scan is no longer limited to the four named provider impls
  la10,"note-greppable",a deliberate simplification is made in code,the author marks it,"the line contains '// NOTE: ... ceiling: ... upgrade: ...' and is grep-findable"
  la11,"rpc-exception-removed","after P3, rpc.rs is inspected",its agent/infra imports are checked,"rpc.rs no longer imports crate::agent or crate::infra and can be removed from arch_guard's exempt_files list"
  la12,"allowlist-blocks-new-violations","an agent file adds a NEW crate::infra import not listed in the allowlist",the guard runs,the build fails and the message names the file and says it is not in the allowlist
  la13,"auth-guidance-not-in-agent","the source tree is inspected for user-guidance message formatting functions",src/agent/ is scanned,"no pure presentation or static help-text module (such as the former agent::auth guidance) remains under agent/"
